issue.title: lsl on ACD is sometimes incomplete

repository.name: rclone
repository.description: "rsync for cloud storage" - Google Drive, S3, Dropbox, Backblaze B2, One Drive, Swift, Hubic, Wasabi, Google Cloud Storage, Azure Blob, Azure Files, Yandex Files

issue.body:
I run a cronjob that lists all files on ACD every twenty minutes to observe any changes (I have some problems with different tools in the past as I am using rclone, syncovery, and arq).

However, every few hours, the output of lsl is incomplete and leaves out files, usually a subset of one directory. During the next run, they are listed again.

When running with -v, nothing suspicious occurs.

I am unable to judge if it is a problem in clone or a problem with ACD.

When filing an issue, please include the following information if
possible as well as a description of the problem.

> What is your rclone version (eg output from `rclone -V`)

1.29

> Which OS you are using and how many bits (eg Windows 7, 64 bit)

Ubuntu 14.04

> Which cloud storage system are you using? (eg Google Drive)

Amazon Cloud Drive

> The command you were trying to run (eg `rclone copy /tmp remote:tmp`)

rclone --stats 0 lsl AmazonCloud:/

> A log from the command with the `-v` flag (eg output from `rclone -v copy /tmp remote:tmp`)

body: The `504 GATEWAY_TIMEOUT` errors are a known problem with ACD itself - see this thread: https://forums.developer.amazon.com/questions/22563/408-request-timeout-errors.html
Just noticed there is a thread on the forum about the 401 errors: https://forums.developer.amazon.com/questions/27740/401-messagetoken-has-expired.html

Tested the -30 beta and the issue is the same and appears to lock even faster than -28.  That could just be a coincidence however.

The only way I've gotten around restarting a transfer is to reauth via rclone config and then try again.

I wonder if there could be a way to just submit a reauth on token failure?  Brute force but seems to work to get things going again at least for another 45 seconds or so.   Same thing though, if the sync dir list is short or null at the front, then the transfers at least commence for the first uploads.  But later on it's near impossible at this point to make and sync changes on large folder sets that have to be read first.

I wonder if we can assign which endpoint we attach too like the fellow in the Amazon forumn.  Could be a cluster setting that has propagated but not to ALL yet perhaps.

Thanks for your amazing product though!  It's been the only solution for me to get backups of my nearly 6TB of data.  I'm only on 3.0TB at present though.

The - 30 beta is supposed to reauth on a 401 error. It obviously isn't working properly yet though - can you post some logs of what happens around the 401 error please? 

As for choosing the endpoint that would be possible. I don't know whether would work though due to the way the underlying s3 storage is structured.
